  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study is designed to determine whether Asians who are especially sensitive to alcohol
      exposure can be protected by boosting their activities of an alcohol disposing enzyme. This
      will be accomplished by administering broccoli sprouts that are rich in an agent that
      increases protective enzyme activity. The test system involves applying alcohol patches to
      the skin and measuring skin redness.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
